WEBVTT

00:00:00.920 --> 00:00:05.870
Well, good evening, everybody. Thank you for joining us again tonight.

00:00:05.871 --> 00:00:13.599
We're going to go over just what the Lord showed us this last time and the heaviness of that video.

00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:35.551
I prayed over it most of the night last night, and we'll continue to pray over it today and for what the Lord has given us with our new assignments of praying for America, praying for President Trump, and continuing to lift our nation up, lifting up other nations, lifting up Canada, and so on and so on.

00:00:35.552 --> 00:00:42.548
It seems like it's a never-ending deal here. But you know, God has chosen us for such a time as this.

00:00:42.549 --> 00:00:47.407
And isn't it wonderful that we have said yes? I'm glad to be here.

00:00:47.408 --> 00:00:50.754
I don't know about y'all; I guess you are because you're here.

00:00:50.755 --> 00:00:57.974
But people wanted to know about the book that Diana was reading from last night because she didn't say.

00:00:57.975 --> 00:01:07.810
She goes, "You know, Braden, I didn't even say which book I was."No, she did at the very end.

00:01:07.811 --> 00:01:11.975
So I wanted to show you real quick. I won't make the broadcast real long tonight.

00:01:11.976 --> 00:01:15.828
I'm trying to keep it shorter because last night was almost three hours.

00:01:15.829 --> 00:01:21.049
I know you all have other things to do than just sitting here with me.

00:01:21.050 --> 00:01:27.726
But we'll just cover things real quick, and then we'll pray and we're just going to lift up the nation.

00:01:27.727 --> 00:01:36.679
This is the book. Let me hold it up here real quick. Can they see it well?

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:45.919
That's the book that she's reading. And when she was reading it last night, this is who she was reading.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:55.049
And it's this man right here. Can you see that? We found it—somebody gave it to us or told us about it in an email.

00:01:55.050 --> 00:02:04.519
I don't know if it was him or whatever, but everybody that I know now is reading this book, especially prayer people.

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:08.494
Pastor Kenneth and them are all reading it. They said they love it.

00:02:08.495 --> 00:02:12.750
I think it's great. There are other people asking about it and wanting to know.

00:02:12.751 --> 00:02:18.138
Let me have it one more time so you can see it. Is it good? Do they have a good photo of it?

00:02:18.139 --> 00:02:29.826
Yeah, so you can see it. You can order it if you feel led to get it. I don't sell books; I don't try to push books.

00:02:29.827 --> 00:02:44.733
I have people send me books from all over the place—self-published books, major book writers, all kinds of people trying to get me to promote their stuff on my channel so that they can sell their book and make money.

00:02:44.734 --> 00:03:01.433
I'm only led whenever the Lord leads us to read something. Diana looks at all of it, and when we're led by the Spirit of the Lord to mention it, it's because it's something that we believe we will use and apply to our own lives.

00:03:01.434 --> 00:03:30.153
Diana and I even told Pastor Kenneth last night, "This is something that I will want to read for the rest of my life, maybe once a month, once every quarter, whatever,"and really try to refresh yourself on what you're feeding on spiritually with the Word and supplements of how to keep yourself stirred up and in that champion mindset.

00:03:30.154 --> 00:03:48.119
I've noticed—and a lot of people, I say it like this—with the gift that God has given me, Brandon doesn't control it, but I'm allowed to see a lot of things that people don't realize that I'm seeing.

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:59.199
And I know, and I know, and I know. Let me ensure that the focus thing is set because I don't want to be disturbed here. I don't want to be a parrot.

00:03:59.200 --> 00:04:10.559
I noticed, just like whenever I study Kathryn Kuhlman a lot and being around Billy Burke and seeing his ministry and how he stands alone.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:14.905
He doesn't have a lot of people in his circle. He's always by himself.

00:04:14.906 --> 00:04:21.958
He's very to himself, very protective over the anointing that is on his life.

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:29.337
He doesn't allow people really in his inner circle. And neither did Sister Kuhlman.

00:04:29.337 --> 00:04:42.519
There is a pioneer work, as I keep learning about all—I'm new to all this and I'm learning so much from the elders and stuff.

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:55.679
It's really easy to be in the place of going, "Oh, we don't touch your glory, Lord,"and you say certain things until you're in a position to touch it.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:05:02.763
You can parrot a lot of things until the glory is on you and pressure comes.

00:05:02.764 --> 00:05:11.333
Flesh always wants to be praised. Regardless of who you are, you always want that 'atta boy'or whatever.

00:05:11.334 --> 00:05:21.525
But I realized that's what Satan was wanting. His whole mission of operation, his M.O., was to be glorified.

00:05:21.526 --> 00:05:29.827
He wanted what God got. He wanted to exalt his kingdom. He wanted to be the Most High.

00:05:29.828 --> 00:05:43.359
"I will be bigger than Him; I'll do this."So, whenever you see people and they parrot things and they say they want end-time glory, they want the revival, they want these things—I watch, and the Lord allows me to see it.

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:56.959
There are so many people that parrot and say they want something that they have no heart for at all. Fruit always displays what your root truly is.

00:05:56.960 --> 00:06:11.639
And I watch a lot of people because to have a revival like John Kilpatrick did at Pensacola back in the '90s, that takes some effort beyond anything that anybody will ever comprehend.

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:19.586
To have a meeting every single day—I don't even know when they had off, or if they ever had off, like Sundays or whatever.

00:06:19.587 --> 00:06:28.039
Probably not Sundays, but if they had an off day, they had to have some rest or they alternated people out.

00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:36.173
But to really have revival in your church and say, "Listen, we're sold out.

00:06:36.174 --> 00:06:39.353
We're going to have church in here 24 hours a day, seven days a week.

00:06:39.354 --> 00:06:54.679
We're going to have revival up in this place,"and not just have these little four-day tent meeting revivals where you go, "Wahoo, we had revival,"and you're kidding yourself.

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:59.759
That's not revival. You had a four-day meeting and you're calling it revival.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:19.882
When the Lord says, "I'm bringing revival to the nation; I'm going to bring a revival to these places,"when I told you I saw Minnesota and he said, "I want to do it in Tennessee and I have Mobile, Alabama again, and I want to use John Kilpatrick again, and I'm going to use these generals"—well, why?

00:07:19.883 --> 00:07:36.274
Because they are sold out. They know what it takes. And the Lord has me praying for these individuals, these men, to be strong like Moses, that their blood will be good, that they will make it to the end, live long, and finish strong.

00:07:36.275 --> 00:07:42.599
But you have a lot of people that have been raised 'churched,'as I want to call them.

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:54.239
There are a lot of churched people that say a lot and say, "Oh, we want this,"but your heart never displays it by the fruit.

00:07:54.240 --> 00:08:02.999
Does that make sense? You can say a lot, but you're not acting it. You don't try to implement what you believe.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:21.679
You can say a lot of things and say, "We want to grow a ministry."Diana said one of the major classes I took in church growth and planting—they always teach you that the first five years of your ministry really determines the whole outcome for the rest of it.

00:08:21.680 --> 00:08:29.919
It's like Joel Osteen. Let me say it like this: Joel Osteen has the largest church in America.

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:37.519
But as he got there, it plateaued. Where did it go any higher?

00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:43.113
What was the cutoff point with the church and how many people started to attend there?

00:08:43.114 --> 00:08:50.399
Is he still growing? Does he have multiple services every single week and it's bigger than Dr.

00:08:50.400 --> 00:09:00.394
Cho's church was in South Korea? There's a point of a climax and it stops in ministry.

00:09:00.395 --> 00:09:14.759
As I'm observing and watching other ministers, they say, "Well, we've been in ministry for 30 years, 20 years, 50 years,"and all this stuff, and you see it, but their ministry is still the same.

00:09:14.760 --> 00:09:23.302
They hit the plateau of where they are and they really have not gone anywhere year after year.

00:09:23.303 --> 00:09:30.163
And you watch certain things, but they talk about the revival. They talk about this and that.

00:09:30.164 --> 00:09:46.005
As a young student, I watch and ask, "How do I implement what I'm learning?"because I'm just starting out and learning from many people.

00:09:46.006 --> 00:09:52.358
I watch big ministries all around now, and I am privy to a lot of conversations that I never was before.

00:09:52.359 --> 00:09:56.640
But I don't want to be a parrot; that's what I'm trying to say.

00:09:56.641 --> 00:10:03.439
When you are a groundbreaker into something that has never been done before—Kathryn Kuhlman was persecuted.

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:14.466
They said she was a witch. They said she's a woman and she can't be used of God because she is a woman. "You can't use a woman."And Kathryn Kuhlman was a woman.

00:10:14.467 --> 00:10:24.519
She went through so much to get where she was—most people would never have been there—but she was sold out, and it was real.

00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:35.919
This is versus somebody who's in ministry that has always been there because their mom and dad were in ministry, so they just followed behind them and inherited what they had.

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:46.512
There's a big difference between being like a Billy Burke—being a trailblazer that is still going strong—and hearing some people that are parrots.

00:10:46.513 --> 00:10:56.498
I watch a lot of parrots; I watch the parrots. But where is it truly at in you when you say, "I want revival"?

00:10:56.499 --> 00:11:02.999
I'm trying to challenge you right now because this is going to cost you something.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:15.399
What we're about to see, what we're about to participate in, is not something that we can just dip in when we feel comfortable with it.

00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:21.572
"Well, the glory's here, brother. Hallelujah!"And then all of a sudden, you're just like, "You know what?

00:11:21.572 --> 00:11:36.439
I feel like going to the movies tonight, and I don't really want to have service because it's not convenient."This isn't going to be convenient.

00:11:36.440 --> 00:11:43.439
I've never had the opportunity to talk to John Kilpatrick about it, but if I ever did, it would be a blessing.

00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:53.560
I always think when I process and watch Azusa, and they said it lasted for so many years and it went every day.

00:11:53.561 --> 00:11:57.735
William Seymour would sit in the corner and put the box on his head and do those things.

00:11:57.736 --> 00:12:09.302
What did it take for this man praying for Finney—what was his name? Nash. This is Nash.

00:12:09.303 --> 00:12:13.118
Finney praying for the revival and him going through for the Great Awakening of America.

00:12:13.119 --> 00:12:21.139
But the Lord said, "I'm going to do a Great Awakening."It's not convenient to be unnoticed. He talks about not being noticed.

00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:29.304
He talks about being the person that is never thanked for the sacrifice of prayer that he did.

00:12:29.305 --> 00:12:44.459
Everybody was always looking at Finney because he was on the stage, saying, "Oh, Finney's so great."But it took Nash praying and doing this cultivation of prayer—the blood, sweat, and tears of prayer.

00:12:44.460 --> 00:12:57.239
I'm talking about the hard work to really be sold out to prayer and not go, "Well, where's my name in lights?"because your flesh always wants to be thanked.

00:12:57.240 --> 00:13:03.649
"Well, I gave this to the ministry. I gave that. I did this. Where's my name in that?

00:13:03.650 --> 00:13:11.448
I held a hand in that."And that's what the Lord was saying: "Are you really truly dead?"When Kathryn Kuhlman said, "I'm dead.

00:13:11.449 --> 00:13:22.338
I don't want to grieve the Holy Spirit."In the things she says—I thought when I watched her at a meeting and she was doing it—there is a guy uploading these things, and I watch her.

00:13:22.339 --> 00:13:32.998
But she really was sold out, and it was never about her. She always says, "I want you to take your eyes off of Kathryn for a moment and realize that you're not here for Kathryn.

00:13:32.999 --> 00:13:43.632
You're here for Jesus."And I watch and I go, "That's not something she's parroting. This was original."But there are a lot of copycats.

00:13:43.633 --> 00:13:58.391
There are a lot of copycats in the prophetic, and they say, "Well, I heard it."And maybe they did, maybe they didn't. But you have to be a pioneer.

00:13:58.392 --> 00:14:07.238
And that's when the Lord said, "Brandon, I've called you to stand alone and do this prayer channel and do what I've called you to do."But always know it's never you; you are the glove.

00:14:07.239 --> 00:14:16.873
I was out doing my yard today, and He said, "Never forget that you're just the glove.

00:14:16.874 --> 00:14:26.639
I am coming in the glove and giving the glove life. Always remember this."I sat there and said, "Yes, Lord, You remind me a lot.

00:14:26.640 --> 00:14:43.988
How thick of a head do I have?"Obviously, if the Father keeps telling you something over and over again, you have to remind yourself. I told Diana tonight, "I don't like tattoos.

00:14:43.989 --> 00:15:05.759
If you get a tattoo, I'm not condemning it, but I just don't want to mark my body up."But I told her tonight that I got a prophetic word from Billy that was very private, and I knew it was smack-dab on because it was one of those words that hits you in the stomach. I told Diana, "I keep forgetting it.

00:15:05.760 --> 00:15:27.559
I've got to get it tattooed on my forearm so every day I can look at that word that God gave me."I know it was the Lord, and I said, "I've got to write it down on my forearm so I can remind myself and never forget what God said."Because time goes by and you become spaced out.

00:15:27.560 --> 00:15:37.532
You get these words, you've got this rhema word from God, and you're just like, "Squirrel!"You're looking at the squirrel over there and you're going, "Oh, I forgot.

00:15:37.533 --> 00:15:44.999
I remember now."Diana goes, "How quickly you forget,"because Diana remembers the words a lot.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:52.519
Diana's very smart, and thank God for her, she always sits out there and counsels me: "This is what the Lord said.

00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:56.792
Do you not remember this?"I say, "Yeah, I do. I remember it very clearly.

00:15:56.793 --> 00:16:11.672
I just sometimes think I can change it through prayer or whatever."But it was a word that the Lord said, and it was private to us.

00:16:11.673 --> 00:16:24.639
I listen to what the Spirit of the Lord said today about the broadcast: praying for you, praying for your seed, praying for whenever somebody blesses me that I'm always diligent about blessing.

00:16:24.640 --> 00:16:35.219
There's a lady who said, "Brandon, I want a baby so bad. My husband and I..."So they sowed a seed to our ministry.

00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:41.519
"Will you please pray for us?"This was several months back, and I was diligent.

00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:51.439
Diana and I both interceded, and she came back. She said, "I just want to let you know we're pregnant.

00:16:51.440 --> 00:17:11.840
The night we sowed the seed, we actually received, and we're expecting our first baby."Diana said, "I want to show you all the people who were believing for children,"because God put it on our heart to pray for you when you want a child and you haven't been able to because of whatever, from the COVID vaccine or whatever.

00:17:11.841 --> 00:17:17.845
There are so many people that have hormone issues right now that cannot conceive.

00:17:17.846 --> 00:17:31.439
You would not believe the list of people believing for children that have never been able to have one and are all of a sudden having a baby—or you're pregnant and they can't find the heartbeat—and we're interceding for you.

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:37.079
Your vine will not cast fruit before its time. We are standing with you.

00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:44.942
But that one person who said, "I've sowed this seed believing,"because they gave a sacrificial gift believing for a child...

00:17:44.943 --> 00:18:00.087
I told Diana that touched me. And when I saw the fruit, they said, "We're pregnant."I'm pregnant. Thank you for being good ground and for praying for us.

00:18:00.088 --> 00:18:15.299
I told Diana, "Those are the ones who come back to tell the Lord thank you."It's not just Brandon and Diana, but it's exciting to hear your testimony and what God did in your life.

00:18:15.300 --> 00:18:29.125
Congratulations. I believe that you'll have a healthy baby and a good, healthy pregnancy. No miscarriages, nothing; that's what I'm trying to say.

00:18:29.126 --> 00:18:35.959
It's interesting—there are so many people with good hearts, and I know the Lord wants a breakthrough in your life.

00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:44.839
I really want to say I played a part in something on the other side, whatever that may be.

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:52.710
I don't always have to be behind a pulpit. I could just be like this, even because I have a camera. I'd pray like this regardless.

00:18:52.711 --> 00:19:02.010
Last night, we prayed and prayed; Diana and I were interceding for most of the night for Boston and the game today, and all the things the Lord showed us.

00:19:02.011 --> 00:19:15.079
We'll go over that. But maybe you can be like this man who just prayed for Finney.

00:19:15.080 --> 00:19:22.834
Never take what you do as nothing. Always give God glory for everything.

00:19:22.835 --> 00:19:31.879
You are a big part of the end-time revival behind this camera as we raise up millions of people and prayer warriors all around this world.

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:40.205
Prayer is what's going to get the manifestation of what we're believing for. I truly believe it.

00:19:40.206 --> 00:19:53.186
I'm always challenged; I try to challenge myself with books and things to stir myself up to always keep at the forefront that it is Him, not you.

00:19:53.187 --> 00:20:23.919
I don't want to be a parrot or someone riding on someone's tailwind—like when you see someone riding in the draft of a semi. I want to be a trailblazer, a pioneer worker.

00:20:23.920 --> 00:20:35.839
There are stones all around, but we're going to make the soil ready with prayer for people who have the anointing to bring them in.

00:20:35.840 --> 00:21:01.079
It's not always going to be fun or noticed, but you may be the one picking the rocks out so the ground is soft and pliable for when the Charles Finneys of this generation or the Billy Grahams come along.

00:21:01.080 --> 00:21:10.959
If that's what God's called me to be—to dig rocks out of the ground and to pray—then we all have our part to play.

00:21:10.960 --> 00:21:20.093
Regardless of whether you are a huge speaker in a big auditorium or not, I don't want to plateau.

00:21:20.094 --> 00:21:39.905
I'm not criticizing Joel; I just know there's a plateau in every ministry unless you keep grabbing and don't become comfortable and satisfied with where you are.

00:21:39.906 --> 00:21:50.319
Pastor Chip always talks about championship teams. Did the Kansas City Chiefs become comfortable after they won so many times?

00:21:50.320 --> 00:22:01.560
Why were they so terrible last year? They had the same players, but they were really bad and weren't fun to watch anymore.

00:22:01.561 --> 00:22:13.685
You become complacent. The Golden State Warriors were good for a while with Steph Curry and were fun to watch.

00:22:13.686 --> 00:22:21.813
You had a dynasty there that fell apart. The same thing happened with Michael Jordan's team.

00:22:21.814 --> 00:22:27.144
I don't ever want to be that championship team that falls apart for the Lord.

00:22:27.145 --> 00:22:38.839
You should always be grabbing, pulling yourself up, going from glory to glory, and not being satisfied with repeating somebody else's words.

00:22:38.840 --> 00:22:57.017
I want to challenge you to keep growing and seeking Him. There's always something new you can learn from the Holy Spirit.

00:22:57.018 --> 00:23:01.399
I like George Washington Carver, the man who talked with the flowers.

00:23:01.400 --> 00:23:06.094
Sister Billie introduced that book, and she always talks about George Washington Carver.

00:23:06.095 --> 00:23:32.374
He was an African-American man during a hard time with prejudice and racism, but he prevailed and was able to succeed whenever most African-Americans weren't.

00:23:32.375 --> 00:23:47.888
He had that bulldog mentality: "I'm going to make it. I don't care what anyone else says; I'm going to do what God's called me to do."I respect George Washington Carver.

00:23:47.889 --> 00:24:11.119
I read his book, "The Man Who Talked with the flowers."My God, that guy went through something in a very racist area, but he never let the racism define him.

00:24:11.120 --> 00:24:18.954
He became what God called him to be. He would get up every morning and talk to the Father, the Great Creator.

00:24:18.955 --> 00:24:32.128
He was a trailblazer. You can't let the color of your skin, your gender, or anything else tell you you're not good enough.

00:24:32.129 --> 00:24:41.279
When God puts His hand on you, I don't care what they say; you will be what God called you to be.

00:24:41.280 --> 00:25:11.319
When I was a janitor, I asked to preach the gospel, and they said, "No, you're a janitor; go clean. I don't see the call on your life."But I felt God told me.

00:25:11.320 --> 00:25:34.133
A lot of people may not see it, but Jesus does, and He said, "I want you to go on YouTube and pray."So, even if people don't acknowledge your call or want you in their inner circle, it doesn't matter.

00:25:34.134 --> 00:25:45.359
I always look for the camaraderie of things. How many times did Brother Kenneth Hagin hang out with Oral Roberts?

00:25:45.360 --> 00:26:06.903
I've never seen them preach together, but they were in the same city, almost on the same street.

00:26:06.904 --> 00:26:13.505
Yet, I hardly ever saw them preaching at each other's conferences. They had some of the biggest ministries.

00:26:13.506 --> 00:26:16.994
I drive by them and get inspired by the mega-church, the grounds, and the school.

00:26:16.995 --> 00:26:28.994
I drive by and look at the City of Faith, the big tower, and the things spinning on the top of the building.

00:26:28.995 --> 00:26:34.592
I drive around Oral Roberts University to keep myself inspired.

00:26:34.593 --> 00:26:57.670
Even if you have the same mission, some camps don't function with other camps.

00:26:57.671 --> 00:27:05.274
I'm learning because I'm in one of the greatest cities in the Bible Belt. And maybe I'm wrong.

00:27:05.275 --> 00:27:10.879
Maybe they hung out every day; I just never saw it on video because I watch all of them.

00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:15.220
But I hardly ever hear them talking about each other very often, even in their sermons.

00:27:15.221 --> 00:27:21.439
But yet they were that close together. You know what I'm saying? I mean, they're like less than five miles apart probably.

00:27:21.440 --> 00:27:26.319
And I'm thinking, because I drive over there, I'm looking and they're almost on the same street.

00:27:26.320 --> 00:27:31.599
But does that make them bad? No. It just means they did what they were called to do.

00:27:31.600 --> 00:27:41.119
And there's a whole lot of other ministries here. There's all kinds of churches in Tulsa. I don't know.

00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:55.835
I'm just learning, and I watch and I say, 'Hmm, this is all so interesting to me.'So people go, 'Well, boy, you treading on really soft, rice paper thin.

00:27:55.836 --> 00:27:59.319
You shouldn't say some of the things you say.'I ain't scared of it.

00:27:59.320 --> 00:28:13.359
I just look at it and I'm just real. I'm not trying to make something out of nothing, but I just watch.

00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:19.719
And like I said, maybe that's why I'm where I'm at and they are where they are at.

00:28:19.720 --> 00:28:32.918
I always ask the hard questions because I want to learn, because I want to go and be close to Him. Y'all have an opinion and it changes all the time.

00:28:32.919 --> 00:28:40.678
The same person who gets excited and tells me I'm good in one email is mad the next couple of days, telling me I'm going to hell.

00:28:40.679 --> 00:28:47.096
And I get them all the time. 'We really like you.'And then the next one, you're mad and you're saying profanity at me in emails.

00:28:47.097 --> 00:29:03.359
And I'm going, 'That's interesting.'D goes, 'Isn't that interesting?'I said, 'No, it's just people.'All right.

00:29:03.360 --> 00:29:11.198
So, be a trailblazer. Be somebody who is getting the rocks out of there like us.

00:29:11.199 --> 00:29:19.719
And when it's all said and done, no matter who's in your tent and who's in your camp, we're in a time like we've never seen before.

